fields.title: About
fields.content:
Mission

RIT Sailing is designed and managed with the intention of allowing students of all skill levels the ability to participate in the sport of sailing while simultaneously building a competitive program in the Middle Atlantic Intercollegiate Sailing Association (MAISA). The club helps to educate students, ranging from no experience to years of it, on the fundamentals of sailing, advanced techniques racing rules and strategies, and experience sailing a variety of boats.

Practices

We hold weekly classroom practices on Thrusday @ 8pm in Gosnell room A200.

We also have frequent on-the-water practices at the Sodus Bay Yacht Club.

Boats

We use a variety of boats including:

  • 420's
  • Lasers
  • Interclubs
  • Club-owned J24

Events

RIT sailors have the opportunity to participate in a number of competitive and leisurely sailing activities. RIT Sailing is active in the Intercollegiate Sailing Association, as well as the Rochester Frostbiting Association, Sodus Bay Ice Boat Club, and is currently exploring ways to become more involved in the local and regional keelboat racing communities.

fields.title: New Website!
fields.sub_title: The new and lovely website that is amazing
fields.content:
Welcome to our new website!

In order to get yourself registered, follow these simple steps:

  1. Go to the register page and register.
  2. Wait until we accept your request (you will be emailed when we do).
  3. Login with your rit google account via the login button found on every page.
  4. You are now registered with the new site.
  5. If you are on the board, email me and I will add you as a staff member.
  6. Once you are added as a staff member (I will tell you) please use the sign out button and sign back in. (This updates your permissions)

If you find any bugs, issues or have any feature requests, please fill out this form.

Your avatar is tied to your Google account so you have to go through Google to change it. When you do, don't press the "Upgrade" button. Once that is done, give Google a few minuites to do the changes, come back, and then logout and back in for the changes to take effect.
